{"title_page": "Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology", "text_new": "'''Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology''', formerly Western University College of Science and Technology, is a public university in [[Kenya]]. The university is named after [[Masinde Muliro]], a Kenyan politician who helped found the school. The University has made great strides to where it is now, best university in Western region, offering world class education. It has approximately 17,000 students across its branches, Main Campus (Kakamega Town), Nairobi Campus, Webuye Campus and Budalangi Campus.\n\n== History ==\n\nMMUST became a fully accredited public university in 2007. Before being elevated to full university status, it was a constituent college of [[Moi University]]. The school was established in January 1972, known as Western College or WECO, a college of Arts and Applied Sciences awarding certificates and diplomas in technical courses.\n\nIn 2002 it became a constituent college of Moi University and changed its name to Western University College of Science and Technology. The university is open to the community to use its resources e.g. the library and other facilities.\n\nIts Vice Chancellor, currently just ended his 5-year term, Prof. Fredrick Otieno. Prof. Joseph Bosire is on acting capacity.\n\n== References ==\nhttp://www.mmust.ac.ke\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Western Province (Kenya)]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Kenya]]\n[[Category:1972 establishments in Kenya]]\n\n\n{{Kenya-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology''', formerly Western University College of Science and Technology, is a public university in [[Kenya]]. The university is named after [[Masinde Muliro]], a Kenyan politician who helped found the school. The University has made great strides to where it is now, best university in Western region, offering world class education. It has approximately 17,000 students across its branches, Main Campus (Kakamega Town), Nairobi Campus, Webuye Campus and Budalangi Campus.\n\n== History ==\n\nMMUST became a fully accredited public university in 2007. Before being elevated to full university status, it was a constituent college of [[Moi University]]. The school was established in January 1972, known as Western College or WECO, a college of Arts and Applied Sciences awarding certificates and diplomas in technical courses.\n\nIn 2002 it became a constituent college of Moi University and changed its name to Western University College of Science and Technology. The university is open to the community to use its resources e.g. the library and other facilities.\n\nIts Vice Chancellor, currently just ended his 5-year term, Prof. Fredrick Otieno. Prof. Joseph Bosire is on acting capacity.\n\n== References ==\nhttp://www.mmust.ac.ke\n\n[[Category:Education in Western Province (Kenya)]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Kenya]]\n[[Category:1972 establishments in Kenya]]\n\n{{Kenya-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masinde_Muliro_University_of_Science_and_Technology"}
